    "_modelScale": "MEASURED uniform world scale for every restaurant GLB (see shared/config/asset-dims.json + tools/measure-glbs.mjs). The KayKit pack is internally consistent, so one factor normalises all of it to the 1.8-unit player: door->2.1, fridge->1.88, chair->0.9, counters/tables->0.75, stove->0.9. Applied in scene.js (native bbox * 0.75, base rested flush at y=0). Surface y-offsets below were re-derived from the resulting surface heights so food sits ON tops, not floating.",
    "_layout": "Same footprint (size 36). Two zones: KITCHEN across the back (z<=-6) and DINING across the front (z>=0), split by a counter/cabinet DIVIDER line at z=-4.5 with two clear walkways (x=-7.5, x=+7.5). Food sits ON surfaces via a y offset = that surface's scaled top (counters/dining tables 0.75, stoves 0.9, sinks ~0.7, the two TALL bar tables large_table/small_table 1.45/1.35). Chairs ring each table facing INWARD: the placement rot points each chair's front at its table centre (the chair GLB's front is +z at rot 0, so an inward chair uses rot = atan2(-dx,-dz) of its offset from centre — the earlier data had these flipped 180deg, seating everyone with their back to the table; corrected here).",
